For this task, I created a digital literacy infographic using Canva. 
The design focused on explaining what digital literacy is, safe internet practices, and useful digital tools for students. 
I included simple icons, short text, and a clean layout to make the information easy to understand.
The infographic highlights the importance of being responsible online and maintaining a professional digital presence.
While creating the infographic, I found it interesting to use design elements like color combinations and icons to visually represent ideas. 
However, it was slightly challenging to organize all the information into a single page without making it look crowded. 
This task helped me understand how visual communication can make complex topics easier to grasp.
